Alvin O. WEST, Appellant v. Claude L. DAWSON, Appellee. No. 16533. United States Court of Appeals District of Columbia Circuit. Argued Nov. 20, 1961. Decided Nov. 30, 1961. Mr. Joseph L. Nellis, Washington, D. C., for appellant. Mr. Dennis Collins, Washington, D. C., with whom Mr. John Paul Sullivan, Washington, D. C., was on the brief, for appellee.

Before Prettyman, Fahy and Dana-her, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

This is an appeal from summary judgment entered by the District Court in a civil action for libel. We find no error.

Affirmed.
